Our Mission

To translate the complexities of reliable brain science into practical and scientifically-credible assessments by providing dependable data that can be utilized with maximum confidence.
MINDSET was created to bring brain
science-based solutions to the forefront of clinical and legal markets while ensuring accurate data collection, specialized data analysis, and objective results.
We operate on a foundational belief in the need for robust and user-friendly solutions and educational support.

Where Vision Meets Innovation: The Story of MINDSET Integrated

2012

THE STORY BEGINS

Mindset Consulting Group is created within The Mind Research Network to serve as a resource for connecting lawyers with reliable brain science data.

2013

A SEED IS PLANTED

Founder and lead neuroscientist begins work on qMRI analyses, which will later evolve into the Quantify MRI processing pipeline.

2017

CASEREVIEW IS BORN

Development of cloud-based software for efficient organizing, interactive indexing, and sharing of medical and legal case records.

2020

INTRODUCING MINDSET INTEGRATED CO.

Launch of MINDSET Integrated Co. as an independent entity, a spin-out from Lovelace Biomedical, with flagship product Quantify leading the forensic brain analysis field.

2022

CELEBRATING 10 YEARS

Expanding and improving, MINDSET announces new hires and releases exciting updates to the Quantify qMRI report and Case Consultation services.

2023

MINDSET CONTINUES TO GROW

Chris N Airriess, PhD joins MINDSET from quantitative imaging industry pioneer Cortechs.ai, bringing extensive expertise and key industry insights to spearhead expansion into new market segments.

2024

LAUNCH OF QLUMINATE

Fully-automated quantitative analysis with end to end integration, delivered directly to radiologists, is now available with QLuminate while an expanding team of experts supports our Case Consultation clients.

2025

LAUNCH OF CASEREVIEW

Unique software platform designed for attorneys, legal teams, and experts to manage multiple facets of case files including complex medical records.

Our team shares a passionate belief

A need for robust and user-friendly tools and educational support exists at the intersection of law and brain injury science. Only the best evidence-based and well-validated science should be available for your use.
